Here's an example of how to use the `onSelected` property:

```
TextField(
  decoration: InputDecoration(
    hintText: 'Enter some text',
  ),
  onSelected: (textSelection) {
    print('Selected text: ${textSelection.text}');
  },
);
```

In this example, the `TextField` widget has an `onSelected` property that is set to a function that takes a `TextSelection` parameter. When the user selects text in the `TextField`, this function will be called and the selected text will be printed to the console.

